The paper focuses on the performance analysis and algorithm design for a vehicular edge computing system, which involves networking, distributed computing, and machine learning. Therefore, cs.NI (networking and internet architecture), cs.DC (distributed, parallel, and cluster computing), and cs.SY (systems and control) are the most likely categories. The paper also uses analytical modeling and learning-based algorithms, which are related to cs.DS (data structures and algorithms) and cs.LG (machine learning).
